  "notes": "Iran has conducted 8 national censuses: 1956, 1966, 1976, 1986, 1996, 2006, 2011, 2016. Iran Data Portal (irandataportal.syr.edu) provides direct downloads for only 3: 1996 (national PDF, Persian only — 'Selected Findings of the National Housing and Population Census'), 2011 (national PDF in English + 31 provincial-level XLS spreadsheets in English, one per province), and 2016 (national PDF 'Selected Findings' in English + 2 XLSX tables: population/households by province and city, and population by age/sex at provincial level). The 1956/1966/1976/1986 census pages on Iran Data Portal exist but contain no direct-download files (navigation stubs only). The 2006 census page has 31 provincial PDFs but they are Persian-only and large (13-91MB each, ~800MB total) — skipped per English-language priority and the 500MB size-discipline rule; not downloaded. amar.org.ir (Statistical Centre of Iran, SCI) was unreachable from this network (curl exit 35 / SSL connect error, also failed via WebFetch with ECONNRESET) — consistent with known geo-blocking of Iranian government sites noted elsewhere in this project's logs; could not verify what SCI hosts directly. IPUMS International (international.ipums.org) confirmed to list Iran census microdata samples for 2006 (2% sample, 1,299,825 person records) and 2011 (2% sample, 1,481,586 person records) only — no other years — at https://international.ipums.org/international-action/sample_details/country/ir; downloading requires free account registration + login, which was NOT performed per task instructions (logged as available-with-registration only). 1996-tehran-census.pdf (Tehran-province subset of the 1996 census, Persian) was found but not downloaded as it is redundant with the national 1996 PDF.",
